# creds — credential request/tracking log

This is NOT a secrets store. Real values go directly into a local,
git-ignored `.env` (see `backend/.env.example` for the full var list) —
never into this file, never into git, never pasted into a chat log that
gets committed. This file only tracks *which* credentials are needed for
which task, their status, and where the real value ends up living. Newest
entries at the bottom. Do not delete or rewrite prior entries.

## Status legend
- NOT NEEDED YET — task builds/tests fully against fixtures/mocks, no
  live credential required to finish or merge.
- REQUESTED — needed for a real (non-mocked) run; asked the human.
- RECEIVED — human supplied it; confirm where it was placed (should
  always be `backend/.env`, which is git-ignored — verify before
  proceeding if this ever says otherwise).

